<h3>Sources of information and preparatory reading</h3>

<ol>
  <li> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eiffel_programming_language">Eiffel programming language</a> </li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.inf.ethz.ch/personal/meyer/#Progress">Eiffel the Language</a> (aka ETL3)</li>
  <li> <a href="http://archive.eiffel.com/doc/oosc/">Object-Oriented
    Software Construction</a>, by Bertrand Meyer (Joe has a copy you
    can borrow, or the library should have a copy or you should buy a
    copy, as it is a critical text for any CS student)</li>
  <li> <a href="http://www.visual-eiffel.org/">Visual Eiffel</a> </li>
  <li> <a href="http://smarteiffel.loria.fr/">SmartEiffel</a> </li>
  
  <li> <a href="http://www.jot.fm/issues/issue_2002_07/column8">The
      Start of an Eiffel Standard</a> by Bertrand Meyer</li>
<li> The draft <a href="http://www.inf.ethz.ch/personal/meyer/publications/ecma/eiffel-standard-2005.pdf">ECMA Eiffel Standard</a></li>
</ol>

